item.description:
This is the most simple use of Moip's marketplace service.
The marketplace is a primary receiver and split the transaction amount with one or more secondary receivers.

In this model, Marketplaces:

- Have liability over chargebacks;
- Have control over refunds;
- Pay Moip fees;

And the merchants:

- Receive part of the transaction.

body.raw:
{
    "ownId": "{{$timestamp}}",
    "amount": {
        "currency": "BRL"
    },
    "items": [
        {
            "product": "Bicicleta Specialized Tarmac 26 Shimano Alivio",
            "quantity": 1,
            "detail": "uma linda bicicleta",
            "price": 2000
        }
    ],
    "customer": {
        "ownId": "{{$timestamp}}",
        "fullname": "Jose Silva",
        "email": "{{$timestamp}}@email.com",
        "birthDate": "1988-12-30",
        "taxDocument": {
            "type": "CPF",
            "number": "22222222222"
        },
        "phone": {
            "countryCode": "55",
            "areaCode": "11",
            "number": "66778899"
        },
        "shippingAddress":   {
                "street": "Avenida Faria Lima",
                "streetNumber": 2927,
                "complement": 8,
                "district": "Itaim",
                "city": "Sao Paulo",
                "state": "SP",
                "country": "BRA",
                "zipCode": "01234000"
            }
    },
    "receivers": [
        {
            "moipAccount": {
                "id": "{{cmerchant_id}}"
            },
            "type": "SECONDARY",
            "amount": {
                "percentual": 50
            }
        }
    ]
}

